The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Thursday, March 06, 2003  Fine Print				 				 				 																Crowe to marry in Fiji																																	 Suva, March 5 (AFP): Gladiator superstar Russell Crowe is to wed his long-time girlfriend, singer Danielle Spencer, in Fiji in the next few weeks, Fiji television reported today.																																	Quoting tourism sources it said the ceremony would occur on the exclusive Waikaya Island, east of the capital Suva. Last year Crowe stayed on the island with Nicole Kidman and her two children just after her marriage with Tom Cruise broke up. As they left, Cruise showed up with his new girlfriend, actress Penelope Cruz. Crowe, 38, proposed during dinner at one of the couples favourite Sydney restaurants the day after he phoned her father, Don Spencer, a local television compere, to tell him first of his plans. The New Zealand-born Oscar winner first met Spencer, who is also an actor, on the sets of the 1990 film The Crossing.
